        {
            "content": "Under the 2015 Paris Agreement countries agreed to set a new, higher annual, climate finance goal by 2025 \u2014 the New Collective Quantified Goal (NCQG) \u2014 scheduled for negotiation at COP29, which starts today. Whilst the majority of climate finance comes from the public sector, according to the Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development (OECD) private capital contributed 20% of the overall investments in 2022, which is the most recent year for which official figures are available. He believes private climate finance in the U.S. will have an even more important role to play when Donald Trump becomes president next year.",
